<TITLE> 6 die in Khagrachhari bus-truck collision </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Khagrachhari, Dec 8 (bdnews24.com)Six people were killed as a bus plunged down a hill after a collision with a truck on the Chittagong-Khagrachhari highway on Monday afternoon, said police. Khagrachhari police sub-inspector Md Iqbal said the collision occurred at Alutilla around 1.30pm, with the hired bus overturning and crashing forty feet down the incline, leaving six of its passengers dead. All the accident victims could not be immediately identified. Among the dead were Tulu Marma (20) and Rafee Chakma 'Sijib' (25). Another passenger was seriously injured and rushed to Chittagong Medical College Hospital. The 45-50 bus passengers were mostly garment workers who had hired the bus to travel home from Chittagong to Khagrachhari for the Eid holidays, said Iqbal. bdnews24
